  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Whenever you succeed at an attack roll made as part of a ghost strike, you can choose to mark the affected creature with necrotic energy as a free action. If a marked creature dies within your dominion range within 1 round per caster level, you can spend 1 spell point as an immediate action to reanimate its body. You can only have a number of creatures marked at a time equal to your casting ability modifier (minimum 1).</p>\n<p>If you possess Sustained Necromancy, you may use this talent to reanimate the body without spending a spell point if you concentrate on it with that talent.</p>\n",
